Irate villagers of Toa Tugawe village in Kisauni, Mombasa County, on Sunday morning beat up a robbery with violence suspect to death. The suspect was said to have been part of a gang that broke into the house of one area resident, Kennedy Chogo, to stage a robbery. Chogo however raised alarm during the 4am incident, prompting fellow villagers to come to his rescue in large numbers. “The villagers descended on one of the robbers injuring him fatally, as the rest staged their escape,” read a police report seen by Citizen Digital. “Detectives are following crucial leads following the incident, with the view of arresting the suspects who escaped with the valuables.” Also Read: Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis